---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Section from "@components/ui/Section.astro";
import Heading from "@components/ui/Heading.astro";
import Button from "@components/ui/Button.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | ArtistWalks"
  description="Artist-led walking experiences in Yerevan exploring modernism, public space and urban history."
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <Section class="max-w-4xl py-20">
    <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-stone-500">ABOUT</p>

    <Heading level={1} class="mt-4">
      Yerevan through the eyes of an artist
    </Heading>

    <p class="mt-8 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700">
      I am a contemporary artist from Yerevan with over 30 years of experience
      as a curator, artist, and theorist. My work focuses on public space and
      modernism, and I have had the opportunity to present it internationally,
      including at the Venice Biennale. My work has also been exhibited in
      leading institutions such as the Contemporary Art Museum in Turin, Italy.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700">
      Yerevan is not just my home; it is a place I am deeply connected to and
      continuously explore — a city I keep returning to through research,
      observation, and artistic practice.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700">
      In my tours, I aim to share a unique perspective on the city — one that
      connects its historical layers with its contemporary identity. Whether you
      are an artist, architecture enthusiast, or curious traveler, I guide you
      through hidden gems, cultural landmarks, and everyday urban life.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700 font-medium">
      Let’s rediscover the city together.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <!-- IMAGE -->
  <Section class="max-w-6xl py-10">
    <img
      src="/images/portrait.jpg"
      alt="ArtistWalks portrait"
      class="w-full rounded-2xl object-cover"
    />
  </Section>

  <!-- PHILOSOPHY -->
  <Section class="max-w-5xl py-16">
    <Heading level={2} class="mb-10"> What shapes these walks </Heading>

    <div class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-3">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Public Space</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-stone-600">
          Architecture and urban planning reveal how cities think, remember, and
          evolve.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Modernism</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-stone-600">
          Soviet and post-Soviet architecture form a layered visual and
          ideological landscape.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Observation</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-stone-600">
          Every walk is an act of reading the city through details, stories, and
          lived experience.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- TESTIMONIALS -->
  <Section class="max-w-5xl py-16">
    <Heading level={2} class="mb-10"> What visitors say </Heading>

    <div class="space-y-10">
      <blockquote class="border-l-2 border-stone-300 pl-6">
        <p class="text-stone-700">
          “Vagram showed us Yerevan from a completely new perspective and
          answered all our questions about the city and the country. Thank you
          very much!”
        </p>
        <footer class="mt-3 text-sm text-stone-500">
          — Daria, March 17, 2026
        </footer>
      </blockquote>

      <blockquote class="border-l-2 border-stone-300 pl-6">
        <p class="text-stone-700">
          “Thank you for the time and immersion into Yerevan’s architecture. We
          saw the city through the eyes of a passionate person.”
        </p>
        <footer class="mt-3 text-sm text-stone-500">
          — Tatyana, March 4, 2026
        </footer>
      </blockquote>

      <blockquote class="border-l-2 border-stone-300 pl-6">
        <p class="text-stone-700">
          “One of the most impressive tours I’ve ever had. It felt like reading
          an entire book about the city.”
        </p>
        <footer class="mt-3 text-sm text-stone-500">
          — Zakharian, February 16, 2026
        </footer>
      </blockquote>

      <blockquote class="border-l-2 border-stone-300 pl-6">
        <p class="text-stone-700">
          “Excellent knowledge of the material. Very polite and intelligent
          guide.”
        </p>
        <footer class="mt-3 text-sm text-stone-500">
          — Laura, February 6, 2026
        </footer>
      </blockquote>

      <blockquote class="border-l-2 border-stone-300 pl-6">
        <p class="text-stone-700">
          “One of the best tours I’ve ever had. Very interesting and
          educational.”
        </p>
        <footer class="mt-3 text-sm text-stone-500">
          — Olga, January 22, 2026
        </footer>
      </blockquote>

      <blockquote class="border-l-2 border-stone-300 pl-6">
        <p class="text-stone-700">
          “A truly professional and insightful guide. Highly recommended for
          anyone interested in architecture and history.”
        </p>
        <footer class="mt-3 text-sm text-stone-500">
          — Galina, January 22, 2026
        </footer>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <Section class="max-w-4xl py-20 text-center">
    <Heading level={2}> Explore Yerevan differently </Heading>

    <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-stone-600">
      Join an ArtistWalks experience and see the city through architecture,
      memory, and everyday life.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-10">
      <Button href="/experiences"> View Experiences </Button>
    </div>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
